</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> IOBOARD_DRAWER defect, replace 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Determine external fault 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Sequentially place connectors and check led to determine which part causes the fault. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check if red led V1 is off 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Red led V1 is continuous on when there is an internal programming problem (FPGA not configured). 
</p><note id="GUID-D6F8CACF-4F7F-4B3D-9002-1BCF71A53B43" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">led will blink shortly during startup (&lt;1 sec). 
</p></note></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">IOBOARD_DRAWER defect, replace 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if yellow led V112 is on 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The physical remote bus link between uMORPF and IOBOARD_DRAWER is active when the led is on. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Check CIS connector X2 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Check RJ45 connector positions 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Check connections and connector 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">RJ45 cable must be connected between IOBOARD_DRAWER (X84) and uMorpf (X6) 
</p></li></ol></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Connect RJ45 cable from X83 to X84 on 12PBA10 (LoopBack RBS) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Connect RJ45 cable from X83 to X84 on 12PBA10 (LoopBack RBS) Create a loopback from RBS master to RBS slave to test the IOBOARD_DRAWER separately (together with RJ45 cable) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The remote bus communication works independently, which means that any master port connected to any slave port can establish a working connection (indicated by active yellow leds). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This can be used to determine which side (master/slave) has the hardware failure. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check if both leds V112,V111 are on 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">15 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">RJ45 cable and/or IOBOARD_DRAWER defect 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">16 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">uMORPF defect, replace 
